<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="581" pageId="8" pageNumber="580" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1918,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1918,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[357,424,1918,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580">Male.</emphasis>
Length (mm): 
<number box="[612,700,1918,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580" value="4.4" valueMax="4.5" valueMin="4.3">4.3–4.5</number>
; thorax, 
<number box="[808,895,1918,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580" value="1.45" valueMax="1.5" valueMin="1.4">1.4–1.5</number>
; wing, 
<number box="[989,1076,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580" value="4.0" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="3.8">3.8–4.2</number>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1092,1156,1918,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1177,1267,1918,1943]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,551,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,551,1740]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 26. Metridius mcalpinei nov. sp., male paratypes. (22). Lateral habitus. (23). Head, lateral view. (24). Wing. (25). Genital capsule, dorsal view with epandrium, proctiger and cerci excluded. (26). Epandrium, proctiger and cerci. Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; ce, cercus; ep, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; gonst, gonostylus; pr, poctiger. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266438/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="580">
Fig. 
<number box="[1235,1267,1919,1943]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580" value="22.0">22</number>
</figureCitation>
). Transversely broadened; ocellar tubercle brown-black, barely raised above eyes, not as prominent as 
<taxonomicName authority="Macquart, 1847" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1847" box="[1175,1332,1954,1978]" class="Insecta" family="Stratiomyidae" genus="Metoponia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robertsoni">
<emphasis box="[1175,1332,1954,1978]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="580">M. robertsoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1343,1429,1954,1979]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580">nov. sp</emphasis>
. Frons and face yellow-brown with short, erect, yellowish setae; frons darkening at vertex. Frontal index 
<number box="[1345,1433,1991,2015]" pageId="8" pageNumber="580" value="0.75" valueMax="0.8" valueMin="0.7">0.7–0.8</number>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
Ratio of frons width to head width 1.0:2.0– 
<number box="[648,684,152,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="2.1">2.1</number>
. Eye height less than head height. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[1192,1275,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,551,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,551,1740]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 26. Metridius mcalpinei nov. sp., male paratypes. (22). Lateral habitus. (23). Head, lateral view. (24). Wing. (25). Genital capsule, dorsal view with epandrium, proctiger and cerci excluded. (26). Epandrium, proctiger and cerci. Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; ce, cercus; ep, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; gonst, gonostylus; pr, poctiger. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266438/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
Fig. 
<number box="[1246,1275,152,176]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="23.0">23</number>
</figureCitation>
) brown, basal half of scape yellowish, swollen orange area of flagellum orange-brown; antennal length about twice as long as head height; antennal scape and pedicel setose, flagellum with long, dense pruinescence; individual flagellomeres, if present, not visible; relative lengths of antennal segments, 
<number box="[831,919,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="3.5" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="3.3">3.3–3.7</number>
:1.0: 
<number box="[961,1081,260,285]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="20.65" valueMax="20.7" valueMin="20.6">20.6–20.7</number>
. Palpus orange.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,294,295,320]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">Thorax.</emphasis>
Yellowish brown with broad, darker brownish band from centre of anepisternum to halter, its margins indistinct. Scutum, katepisternum ventrally, anepisternum posteriorly, scutellum and laterotergite with long, fine, yellowish setae. Scutum and scutellum punctate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">Legs yellow-brown; all femora and hind tibia darkened towards apex and with yellowish setae. First tarsomere on all legs much shorter than tibia.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,264,476,501]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[279,364,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,551,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,551,1740]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 26. Metridius mcalpinei nov. sp., male paratypes. (22). Lateral habitus. (23). Head, lateral view. (24). Wing. (25). Genital capsule, dorsal view with epandrium, proctiger and cerci excluded. (26). Epandrium, proctiger and cerci. Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; ce, cercus; ep, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; gonst, gonostylus; pr, poctiger. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266438/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
Fig. 
<number box="[332,364,476,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hyaline, membrane entirely with microtrichia; veins R 
<number box="[998,1006,491,505]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="1.0">1</number>
and R 
<number box="[1079,1087,491,505]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[1096,1103,491,505]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="5.0">5</number>
setulose on upper surface, R 
<number box="[1428,1436,491,505]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="2.0">2</number>
bare; R 
<number box="[234,248,514,539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="4.0">4</number>
+ 
<number box="[264,277,514,539]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="5.0">5</number>
unbranched. Discal medial cell absent. Halter long, pale yellowish. Alula narrow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,323,550,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Brownish with pale yellowish setae. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[756,888,550,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">Terminalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[904,1038,550,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 26" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1762,1785]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,551,1702]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,551,1740]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 26. Metridius mcalpinei nov. sp., male paratypes. (22). Lateral habitus. (23). Head, lateral view. (24). Wing. (25). Genital capsule, dorsal view with epandrium, proctiger and cerci excluded. (26). Epandrium, proctiger and cerci. Abbreviations: aed, aedeagus; ce, cercus; ep, epandrium; goncx, gonocoxite; gonst, gonostylus; pr, poctiger. Scale bar, 0.25 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/266438/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
Figs 
<number box="[964,1038,550,575]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" value="25.5" valueMax="26.0" valueMin="25.0">25–26</number>
</figureCitation>
). More or less spherical; brownish yellow. Cerci one-segmented. Gonostyli stocky, truncate at apex and concave in inner surface. Aedeagus single pronged. Gonocoxite medially attenuate distally, extending almost to apex of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,863]" box="[199,418,658,683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,658,683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,863]" box="[199,295,694,719]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">Biology.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,863]" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">
Males have been taken by sweeping the grass-like stems of settlers flax, 
<taxonomicName box="[1006,1254,731,755]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Gymnostachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anceps">
<emphasis box="[1006,1254,731,755]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="581">Gymnostachys anceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R.Br. (
<taxonomicName box="[1333,1428,731,755]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="9" pageNumber="581" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Araceae</taxonomicName>
) growing in rain forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
